title: "Js2coffee: convert JavaScript code to CoffeeScript"
---
- content_for :head do
  != style_tag 'css/style.css'

%a.github{href: "http://github.com/rstacruz/js2coffee"} Fork me on GitHub

%hgroup#heading
  %h1 Js2Coffee
  %h5 The JavaScript to CoffeeScript compiler.

%nav#tabs
  %ul
    %li
      %a.active{:href => "#js2coffee"}!= "JS &rarr; Coffee"
    %li
      %a{:href => "#coffee2js"}!= "Coffee &rarr; JS"

#editors
  %form#js2coffee
    .error.hide#js2coffee_error
    %pre.editor.left#js2coffee_editor
    %pre.output.right#js2coffee_output

  %form#coffee2js.hide
    .error.hide#coffee2js_error
    %pre.editor.left#coffee2js_editor
    %pre.output.right#coffee2js_output

  %br

%section#info
  %h2
    Js2coffee

  %article
    %h3 Info
    %p
      Js2coffee helps you migrate projects to 
      %a{href: 'http://www.coffeescript.org'} CoffeeScript
      by compiling your JavaScript code into CoffeeScript.

    %p
      Js2coffee is a project of
      %a{href: '/'} Rico Sta. Cruz.
      The source code is available over at
      %a{href: 'http://github.com/rstacruz/js2coffee'} GitHub.

  %article
    %h3 Local usage
    %p
      Js2coffee is also available as a Node.JS module.
    %pre
      $ npm install js2coffee
      $ js2coffee file.js > file.coffee

  %article
    :markdown
      ### Reporting issues
      Please report any issues you find over to the [Js2coffee issue tracker](http://github.com/rstacruz/js2coffee/issues).
      As a courtesy to everyone, be sure to check if your problem has already been reported.

  -# %article
  -#   %h3 Caveats
  -#   %p Please take note of a few inconsistencies that may happen during conversion.
  -# 
  -#   %ul
  -#     %li
  -#       :markdown
  -#         #### `==` in CoffeeScript is `===` in JavaScript
  -#         There is no way to emulate the `==` behavior in CoffeeScript. As such, consider
  -#         all equality checks to be strict.
  -# 
  -#     %li
  -#       :markdown
  -#         #### Labels are not supported in CoffeeScript
  -#         Code like `function() { test1: ... }` will not compile.

%script{type: 'text/javascript', charset: 'utf-8', src: 'https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.5.1/jquery.min.js'}
%script{type: 'text/javascript', charset: 'utf-8', src: 'http://ajax.cdnjs.com/ajax/libs/underscore.js/1.1.5/underscore-min.js'}

